1
00:00:06,840 --> 00:00:09,160
You’ve done some impressive work.

2
00:00:10,320 --> 00:00:12,520
You even won a short film competition.

3
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:15,800
You used to work in directing,

4
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:19,320
but you didn’t complete the project.

5
00:00:21,880 --> 00:00:24,000
And you haven’t worked for three years now?

6
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:30,760
Well, at that time, I had to quit
to help out with things at home.

7
00:00:31,680 --> 00:00:34,640
That’s why I decided to work
part-time at a suit shop instead,

8
00:00:34,720 --> 00:00:36,760
so I could take care of
things at home more easily.

9
00:00:38,320 --> 00:00:39,720
But now, I don’t have to anymore,

10
00:00:40,960 --> 00:00:42,840
so I’m looking forward
to getting back to work.

11
00:00:43,040 --> 00:00:44,960
So, your home situation is sorted?

12
00:00:48,160 --> 00:00:49,160
Yes.

13
00:00:50,880 --> 00:00:51,880
Well…

14
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:55,360
I broke up with my partner recently,

15
00:00:57,240 --> 00:00:59,600
so I’m now ready to start working again.

16
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:02,680
I’m fully committed to
giving my best at work.

17
00:01:05,960 --> 00:01:08,520
I’m fine starting as an Assistant 3,

18
00:01:08,600 --> 00:01:14,440
and in 2-3 years, you can evaluate
whether I’m ready to move up to director.

19
00:01:17,880 --> 00:01:19,680
Let me be honest with you.

20
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:22,400
I invited you for this interview

21
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:24,800
because we’re truly
interested in your work,

22
00:01:24,880 --> 00:01:28,560
and we’re curious where you have
been during the time you stopped working,

23
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:31,520
but after learning your reason,

24
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:33,680
I’m hesitant to hire you.

25
00:01:36,520 --> 00:01:38,840
We’re worried that after we hire you

26
00:01:38,920 --> 00:01:41,360
and you start dating again,

27
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:43,160
you might quit your job once again.

28
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:50,040
Our company is looking for
someone who’s serious about work,

29
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:51,760
not someone who does it just for fun.

30
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:54,320
If you want the job,

31
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:56,800
next time, you don’t
need to be this honest.

32
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:16,920
Well, you failed again?

33
00:02:20,520 --> 00:02:21,640
Yes.

34
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:25,120
If it’s that hard to find a job,
why not start your own business?

35
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:29,160
Look at this guy.

36
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:32,280
I think he’s about your age.

37
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:33,680
He’s Earn, the owner of EarnChop.

38
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:37,680
And here are the features
of our app, EarnChop.

39
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:41,480
Apart from making video editing easier,

40
00:02:41,560 --> 00:02:44,080
- it will also make your videos unique.
- He’s cool.

41
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:45,376
He deserves to be a role model.

42
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:49,080
It’s perfect for beginners
or even for experts.

43
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:50,560
Turning your VDOs into…

44
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:52,520
Here you are.

45
00:02:52,600 --> 00:02:54,160
Two for you, as usual.

46
00:02:57,840 --> 00:03:00,720
Well, I’m living alone now.

47
00:03:02,040 --> 00:03:03,040
Pardon?

48
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:06,760
Nothing.

49
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:28,120
BEW

50
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:31,160
This week is the alumni gathering.
I’ve already booked for everyone.

51
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:33,040
Let me know if anyone
is bringing a plus one.

52
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:35,560
Po, will I see you there?

53
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:37,320
AUGUS

54
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:44,720
MOM

55
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:51,680
Hello, Mom?

56
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:55,360
Po, how was your job interview yesterday?

57
00:05:57,280 --> 00:05:59,400
I got the offer already, Mom. Don’t worry.

58
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,240
Really?

59
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:03,240
I knew you’d make it.

60
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:06,440
So, how is it? When are
you starting your new job?

61
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:08,720
Well,

62
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:11,440
it’s next Monday.

63
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:13,600
Monday?

64
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:18,960
PUBLIC HOLIDAY - COMPENSATORY HOLIDAY

65
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,200
Good luck on your job, then.

66
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:25,640
Thank you.

67
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,336
MONEY TRANSFERRED IN FROM
SAVINGS ACCOUNT 0803-xxxx-xxx

68
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:36,560
AMOUNT: 10,000 BAHT

69
00:06:36,640 --> 00:06:38,400
Take this for now, son.

70
00:06:38,480 --> 00:06:41,440
INCOMING TRANSACTION: AMOUNT 10,000
THB MOM: USE THIS FOR NOW, SWEETHEART.

71
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:03,456
MONEY TRANSFERRED IN FROM
SAVINGS ACCOUNT 0127-xxxx-xxx

72
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:05,416
-AMOUNT: 10,000 BAHT -Good
luck with your job search.

73
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:07,560
Eh? What’s with that face?

74
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:13,600
I'm already this old, and my
parents are still sending me money.

75
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:17,400
If I were you,

76
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:19,680
with parents taking care of me this much,

77
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:21,480
I wouldn't bother looking for a job.

78
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:25,960
I need to work and pay them
back the money anyway, Uncle.

79
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:29,760
Who would do what you did,

80
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:33,480
telling the truth, so they
ended up not hiring you?

81
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:37,560
They would think you’re
clingy to your partner.

82
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:40,280
But you really are clingy, huh?

83
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:42,760
You pushed him until he became the CEO.

84
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,720
Next time, don’t tell them everything,

85
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:49,880
or you’ll end up working here forever

86
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:52,880
and never get the job you want. Got it?

87
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:04,240
Po, I’ve got work for you.

88
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:07,440
I want a job, but not from you.

89
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:09,120
I told you to do it, so just do it.

90
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:10,280
Now, turn on your computer.

91
00:08:16,960 --> 00:08:18,720
Okay, fade in.

92
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:20,440
Then, insert a text.

93
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:22,560
Add an effect, too.

94
00:08:22,640 --> 00:08:24,600
Make it cool, not dull.

95
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:28,280
As for me, I hope you get caught.

96
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:31,120
Before I get caught, add
the sound effect for me first.

97
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:33,000
It’s in the second file.

98
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:35,640
Let’s go with… verse 2.

99
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:36,840
It’s an exciting verse.

100
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:40,960
This one?

101
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:46,680
Don’t do anything beyond my instructions!

102
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:51,360
Which account is she dealing
with? That sounds pretty intense.

103
00:09:10,040 --> 00:09:12,200
Dude, my kiddos are so cute!

104
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:13,640
This is it!

105
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:17,080
The future of the T-POP industry is
definitely promising because of my kiddos!

106
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:19,960
Look at my bias!

107
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:21,280
Pepper, my son!

108
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:23,040
He’s lovey-dovey adorable!

109
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:26,000
By the way,

110
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:29,800
you've been editing so many clips for me.

111
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:30,960
Don't you feel anything?

112
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:34,000
There must be someone you’re attracted to.

113
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:36,800
I’ll let you pick your bias.

114
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:38,400
Choose one.

115
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:40,080
These five?

116
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:59,120
I don’t really have a favorite.

117
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:10,160
How could you not fall for my kiddos?

118
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:15,040
Fine. That’s up to you.

119
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:16,536
MONEY TRANSFERRED IN FROM
SAVINGS ACCOUNT 4133-xxxx-xxx

120
00:10:16,560 --> 00:10:17,920
That’s your pay.
AMOUNT: 7,760 BAHT

121
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:21,280
You're another one.

122
00:10:22,040 --> 00:10:23,760
-Stop sending me money already. -Eh?

123
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:28,080
I hired you to work, so I must pay you.

124
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:31,080
Why? Or do you want
to work for me for free?

125
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:32,240
Just forget about it.

126
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:34,800
You must go to the alumni
gathering this Saturday.

127
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:38,960
Tell our friends you’re working with me,

128
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:40,640
so you’ll get to go out and meet people.

129
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:42,840
Maybe you'll even find yourself a new guy.

130
00:10:44,160 --> 00:10:45,456
But I literally have nothing now.

131
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:47,040
If you have nothing,

132
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:49,120
at least you might get yourself a guy.

133
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:58,440
I’ll hang up now. Work’s in.

134
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,400
What is it?

135
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:05,720
Baifern, Mick, MARS’
manager, is here to see you.

136
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:08,640
Okay, sure. I’ll be there in a minute.

137
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:17,656
By the way, which account
were you dealing with just now?

138
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:18,920
That was so intense.

139
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,160
Account M.

140
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:24,040
-Which M? -No idea.

141
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:28,240
Hello, Mr. Mick.

142
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:29,320
Hello, Miss Baifern.

143
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:32,000
-Please make yourself at home. -Thank you.

144
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:35,400
Today, I brought a gift basket
to thank you for choosing MARS

145
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:37,960
as the new product's brand ambassador.

146
00:11:38,040 --> 00:11:39,896
The members actually
wanted to come themselves,

147
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:42,600
but their schedule has
been really tight recently.

148
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:44,880
We’re preparing for a big project now.

149
00:11:44,960 --> 00:11:46,520
A big project?

150
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:48,080
Can you drop a little spoiler?

151
00:11:48,160 --> 00:11:49,800
I can’t, Miss Baifern.

152
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:53,160
But I’m under stress now

153
00:11:53,240 --> 00:11:56,280
because I still haven’t found
a talented documentary director.

154
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:59,200
I want a director to film
the footage of the members.

155
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:03,760
Is it that hard to find?

156
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:05,240
Exactly.

157
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:08,880
The person must keep the project secret.

158
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:12,200
You know, people these days
can’t keep things quiet.

159
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:14,560
You’re right.

160
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:20,400
But actually, I know
someone who is qualified.

161
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:23,880
Would you like their contact information?

162
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,080
Hurry up, dude.

163
00:12:29,520 --> 00:12:30,520
Hey.

164
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:32,400
Can we not do this?

165
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:34,600
You found me a job,

166
00:12:35,280 --> 00:12:37,120
but it's about digging
up information on MARS?

167
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:39,600
I’m not making you
dig up their information.

168
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:42,840
I just want you to have
a good life and get hired.

169
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:46,800
I believe in you.

170
00:12:46,880 --> 00:12:48,320
If you do this job well,

171
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:50,720
you'll become so famous and successful

172
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:52,776
that you can even step all
over that jerk Earn’s face,

173
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:54,040
the one who said you suck, man.

174
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:55,640
You’re a new person now,

175
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:58,400
about to film a documentary for MARS!

176
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:02,080
You must get hired, no matter what.

177
00:13:02,160 --> 00:13:03,920
This is what you need to say

178
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:06,800
because it’s what I’ve
sold to Mick about you.

179
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:10,720
Oh? What did you say to him?

180
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:12,280
You made up my profile.

181
00:13:12,360 --> 00:13:14,720
How real do you want your profile?

182
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:18,360
Do you want me to include you
creating a logo for that jerk Earn,

183
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:19,520
who dumped you afterward?

184
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:22,440
No, thanks.

185
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:24,680
Then go with my version.

186
00:13:24,760 --> 00:13:27,520
It's based on a true story. Let’s go.

187
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:31,680
Hurry up. My kiddos are waiting.

188
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:39,776
MR. PAWAT NUENGANAN INTERESTED
POSITION: VIDEO DIRECTOR

189
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:42,080
You won a short film competition.

190
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:44,080
After that,

191
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:47,720
you have been highly experienced in
the fashion industry for four years.

192
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:49,480
What did you do?

193
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:54,160
Previously, I used to shoot
private sessions for celebrities.

194
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:56,640
You’re Mr. Sombat, right?

195
00:13:57,880 --> 00:14:00,720
I’ve been a fan of your dramas for ages.

196
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:02,416
- Po, come take some pictures for me.
- Sure. My pleasure.

197
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:04,160
One, two, three.

198
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:07,600
I also used to take candid
behind-the-scenes shots for artists.

199
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:14,280
Also, I added effects
and did some editing work.

200
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:16,240
That’s a well-rounded
set of skills you’ve got.

201
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:20,240
By the way, since you want to
work with Oner Entertainment,

202
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:22,280
how well do you know us?

203
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:29,000
Oner Entertainment is a full-fledged
entertainment industry company.

204
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:34,640
It includes solo artists,

205
00:14:34,720 --> 00:14:36,160
boy bands, and girl groups.

206
00:14:37,560 --> 00:14:39,240
The artist that has gained the most fame

207
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:42,280
and made the most money is MARS.

208
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:52,080
MARS has been successful
since their second album.

209
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:54,480
Their song was a massive hit.

210
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:56,720
Everyone can sing along
and dance to their song.

211
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:06,000
The advertising work is pouring in,

212
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:08,000
and as for photoshoots,
don’t even mention it,

213
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:10,000
big-name brands are reaching out.

214
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:13,320
So, MARS is the top income
generator for the company

215
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:16,760
because the five of them are the
perfect formula for an idol group.

216
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:20,360
Jun is a supporting vocalist,

217
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:21,760
with a friendly and playful look.

218
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:23,920
He’s a bit cheeky but full of charisma.

219
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:26,920
Dylan is the group’s rapper.

220
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:29,440
He’s taciturn, speaks little,
and finds it hard to smile,

221
00:15:29,520 --> 00:15:31,960
but it's that indifferent
look that wins the fans' hearts.

222
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:34,840
Pepper is a heart-warming all-rounder.

223
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:36,456
He’s such a gentle friend.

224
00:15:36,480 --> 00:15:38,120
Just seeing him already warms your heart.

225
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:42,040
Nano is the main dancer, the
golden maknae of the group.

226
00:15:43,160 --> 00:15:44,440
Though he’s the youngest,

227
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:45,360
he’s lively,

228
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:47,176
with an impressive performance
that is way beyond his years.

229
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:51,240
Lastly, Thame is the group leader,
who is the heart and soul of the group.

230
00:15:51,880 --> 00:15:54,640
He excels at both singing and
dancing with a handsome look.

231
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:59,680
He’s definitely the most
well-rounded leader T-pop has ever seen.

232
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:03,240
MARS is also known for being united.

233
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:05,640
The members love each other a lot.

234
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:08,400
After the five gathered,

235
00:16:09,320 --> 00:16:10,960
their chemistry turned out super perfect.

236
00:16:17,640 --> 00:16:20,840
Did I… say something wrong?

237
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:24,440
Hey,

238
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:27,840
are you a fan pretending
to apply for a job?

239
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:36,440
You really can’t let him know you
once worked for a fanbase account.

240
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:41,560
This company is really serious about
fans pretending to be part of the staff.

241
00:16:43,160 --> 00:16:45,416
I did stalk and photograph
them once at an event for you.

242
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:48,600
- Do you think they’ll remember my face?
- You only went once,

243
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:49,976
and when it was time to see them,

244
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,000
you put your camera away.

245
00:16:51,040 --> 00:16:53,080
There were thousands of fans,

246
00:16:53,160 --> 00:16:54,400
so they wouldn’t recognize you.

247
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:58,240
Anyway, you need to be careful

248
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:01,400
and make sure not to slip up!

249
00:17:07,680 --> 00:17:09,760
Once I found out I had to work with MARS,

250
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:12,040
I made sure to do my homework in advance,

251
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:16,480
but due to the tight timeline,

252
00:17:17,119 --> 00:17:19,359
I was only able to learn this much.

253
00:17:20,480 --> 00:17:21,480
All right.

254
00:17:22,359 --> 00:17:23,440
Let’s get down to it.

255
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:25,920
What is your expected salary?

256
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:33,880
Nice.

257
