-Well, that day… -Stop it already.

519
00:36:45,880 --> 00:36:49,960
I think you should
explain this to Miss Pemika.

520
00:36:53,120 --> 00:36:54,120
Hand it to me,

521
00:36:55,760 --> 00:36:57,560
so my group’s reputation won’t be ruined

522
00:36:58,440 --> 00:36:59,840
because of a sasaeng like you.

523
00:37:07,920 --> 00:37:08,960
Hand it to me.

524
00:37:15,360 --> 00:37:18,360
PAWAT NUENGANAN, CREATIVE

525
00:37:30,920 --> 00:37:32,280
Even if I weren’t here,

526
00:37:35,600 --> 00:37:38,560
your group’s reputation would still
be ruined because of you, wouldn’t it?

527
00:37:42,160 --> 00:37:43,160
What?

528
00:37:45,160 --> 00:37:46,320
You're claiming that

529
00:37:47,360 --> 00:37:49,440
you don't want your group’s
reputation to be ruined,

530
00:37:50,760 --> 00:37:52,000
but in reality,

531
00:37:53,240 --> 00:37:55,200
you just don't want yours to be ruined

532
00:37:56,560 --> 00:37:57,840
because I happen to know

533
00:37:59,680 --> 00:38:01,440
how selfish you are.

534
00:38:12,160 --> 00:38:13,400
You're just…

535
00:38:17,160 --> 00:38:20,120
someone who, after becoming a
little more successful than others,

536
00:38:27,560 --> 00:38:31,160
forgets that the people
who've been with you…

537
00:38:32,520 --> 00:38:33,720
also have feelings.

538
00:38:37,120 --> 00:38:39,760
Thank you, everyone, for coming
to the launch event of my company.

539
00:38:40,640 --> 00:38:42,280
Thank you for all the support,

540
00:38:42,880 --> 00:38:45,320
whether from our sponsors, clients,

541
00:38:45,920 --> 00:38:47,200
and…

542
00:38:51,640 --> 00:38:53,640
all the kind prominent
figures in the IT industry.

543
00:38:54,360 --> 00:38:56,720
Thank you very much. Cheers!

544
00:38:59,160 --> 00:39:01,000
They’ve never cared about

545
00:39:02,040 --> 00:39:03,800
how the people behind them feel.

546
00:39:04,840 --> 00:39:07,440
Someone like you is exactly the type

547
00:39:09,080 --> 00:39:14,000
who never values those who’ve
been on this journey with you.

548
00:39:14,080 --> 00:39:15,096
I just don’t like the font.

549
00:39:15,120 --> 00:39:16,520
And can you make it smaller?

550
00:39:16,600 --> 00:39:17,680
It overlaps with the logo.

551
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:20,280
And what’s this? Where does it
reflect the essence of EarnChop?

552
00:39:26,560 --> 00:39:27,640
TAKE CARE OF IT!

553
00:39:30,040 --> 00:39:31,040
Be honest with me.

554
00:39:32,360 --> 00:39:33,760
How could you do that?

555
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:37,800
When the opportunity suddenly came,

556
00:39:38,720 --> 00:39:41,400
you chose to leave those who
have been with you for so many years

557
00:39:41,480 --> 00:39:42,960
and get by alone.

558
00:39:48,200 --> 00:39:49,200
Can we talk?

559
00:39:50,480 --> 00:39:52,000
-Just now, you… -Uncle.

560
00:39:52,680 --> 00:39:53,800
-Hello. -Hi.

561
00:39:54,480 --> 00:39:56,416
Have you got any suggestion
for a new entrepreneur like me?

562
00:39:56,440 --> 00:39:59,400
What about the things others did for
you when you had more jobs coming in?

563
00:39:59,800 --> 00:40:01,880
Aren’t they meaningful
to you, even a little?

564
00:40:15,720 --> 00:40:17,360
Thank you for everything this whole time.

565
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:20,200
You know what?

566
00:40:20,280 --> 00:40:21,280
What you’ve done

567
00:40:23,040 --> 00:40:25,400
makes it impossible for the
people behind you to understand

568
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:29,720
why they’ve wasted so many years with you,

569
00:40:30,360 --> 00:40:32,200
doing things for you.

570
00:40:38,360 --> 00:40:40,240
You’re so damn selfish.

571
00:40:40,320 --> 00:40:42,240
You have no right to say this

572
00:40:43,400 --> 00:40:44,496
while you totally know nothing.

573
00:40:44,520 --> 00:40:45,640
I know.

574
00:40:46,680 --> 00:40:50,000
I know exactly what kind of person you are!

575
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:58,000
I also know

576
00:40:59,320 --> 00:41:00,760
how painful it is…

577
00:41:02,560 --> 00:41:03,800
for those who are left behind.

578
00:41:03,880 --> 00:41:05,880
How about the person who has to leave them?

579
00:41:08,960 --> 00:41:10,240
Don’t you think that hurts, too?

580
00:41:38,600 --> 00:41:39,960
To get to this point,

581
00:41:41,280 --> 00:41:42,560
do you think it has been easy?

582
00:41:49,040 --> 00:41:53,960
Of course, it’s easy to understand
the pain those who get left behind get,

583
00:41:59,040 --> 00:42:00,400
but the one who does the leaving

584
00:42:03,720 --> 00:42:05,080
is just as hurt.

585
00:42:48,320 --> 00:42:51,160
So, I’ve booked you for the
alumni gathering this Saturday.

586
00:42:51,240 --> 00:42:53,720
Brag to everyone that you're a director.

587
00:42:53,800 --> 00:42:57,040
Spill the tea about how awful
that jerk Earn is to everyone.

588
00:43:03,000 --> 00:43:04,856
THIS WEEK IS THE ALUMNI GATHERING
I’VE ALREADY BOOKED FOR EVERYONE

589
00:43:04,880 --> 00:43:06,680
LET ME KNOW IF ANYONE
IS BRINGING A PLUS ONE

590
00:43:15,160 --> 00:43:18,520
-Hey, I have a question. -What is it?

591
00:43:22,520 --> 00:43:24,160
Does the person who leaves others behind…

592
00:43:26,080 --> 00:43:27,320
feel hurt?

593
00:43:29,240 --> 00:43:30,720
What mood are you in, huh?

594
00:43:31,560 --> 00:43:33,560
Or did that jerk Earn
say something to you again?

595
00:43:34,760 --> 00:43:35,960
It has nothing to do with him.

596
00:43:37,440 --> 00:43:38,440
I’m just curious.

597
00:43:42,280 --> 00:43:47,680
How could someone who does that feel hurt?

598
00:43:49,280 --> 00:43:50,640
So, he did that?

599
00:43:51,520 --> 00:43:52,880
You used a trump card, didn’t you?

600
00:43:52,920 --> 00:43:53,760
It was a trump card.

601
00:43:53,840 --> 00:43:55,400
Come on, I just didn’t want to work.

602
00:43:55,480 --> 00:43:56,600
And if they feel hurt,

603
00:43:58,640 --> 00:43:59,800
why would they do it?

604
00:44:02,480 --> 00:44:03,640
I don’t know.

605
00:44:04,200 --> 00:44:06,960
If you’re curious, ask them.

606
00:44:36,200 --> 00:44:38,440
I KNOW ONER

607
00:45:23,200 --> 00:45:24,200
Tell me

608
00:45:25,600 --> 00:45:27,680
if you’re just a fan or a sasaeng.

609
00:45:31,000 --> 00:45:32,640
Neither.

610
00:45:36,960 --> 00:45:37,960
It’s true

611
00:45:38,600 --> 00:45:40,320
that I once got hired by your fan

612
00:45:41,040 --> 00:45:42,560
and attended your event.

613
00:45:44,960 --> 00:45:46,240
But it was only once.

614
00:45:49,960 --> 00:45:51,520
I didn’t think you’d remember me.

615
00:45:58,040 --> 00:45:59,800
That’s because you’re
different from others.

616
00:46:15,920 --> 00:46:17,000
Yeah?

617
00:46:23,120 --> 00:46:24,200
Anyway,

618
00:46:25,320 --> 00:46:27,000
I’m not doing that anymore.

619
00:46:29,360 --> 00:46:30,480
I just…

620
00:46:31,120 --> 00:46:33,120
Just continue your job, then.

621
00:46:40,680 --> 00:46:41,720
You’re doing well.

622
00:46:44,280 --> 00:46:47,840
You’ve made me see my members
in a way I haven’t in a long time.

623
00:46:51,120 --> 00:46:52,320
I think I can manage.

624
00:46:53,120 --> 00:46:54,560
-That’s a contrasting color. -Okay.

625
00:46:54,640 --> 00:46:56,200
Cut, cut. Thank you so much.

626
00:47:24,960 --> 00:47:26,600
If you want me to continue with this job,

627
00:47:29,160 --> 00:47:31,320
the person I want to get to know the most…

628
00:47:34,720 --> 00:47:35,880
is you.

629
00:48:03,320 --> 00:48:04,696
Yesterday, I still didn't
get any good footage.

630
00:48:04,720 --> 00:48:08,080
We’ve got no time left, Po.
Thame is heading to Korea soon.

631
00:48:09,280 --> 00:48:11,840
But I’ve only known Thame for a day.

632
00:48:16,760 --> 00:48:18,440
If you want to interview him, do it now.

633
00:48:21,600 --> 00:48:23,400
Honestly, how do you feel?

634
00:48:26,480 --> 00:48:27,640
I'm sorry.

635
00:48:30,280 --> 00:48:31,960
I'm sorry, back then, I thought…
